› [Image #1] why is it not coming in relevant and coming in already processed


• Because the agent has already processed and stored those 12 relevant emails earlier.

  The pipeline checks SQLite first:

  message_id already exists? -> skip as already_processed

  So on this run:

  "read": 27,
  "relevant": 0,
  "already_processed": 12

  means:

  - It read all 27 emails from mock Graph.
  - 12 relevant trade emails were already stored in a previous run.
  - So it skipped them instead of storing duplicate case folders.
  - This proves deduplication is working.

  You can confirm the 12 relevant cases already exist by testing:

  GET /storage/cases

  If you want a fresh first-run result again, reset the output database and processed folders, then rerun. In cmd:

  del data\email_index.db
  rmdir /s /q data\processed
  mkdir data\processed

  Then in Swagger run again:

  POST /agent/run

  Body:

  {
    "source": "graph"
  }

  Then you should get:

  "relevant": 12,
  "already_processed": 0


